                            <comment id="13467134" author="tjake" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 19:46:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How deeply do we want to fix this? It goes pretty deep into how we deal with isReversed flag vs ReversedType.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can, however easily fix it in the CQLParser by just flipping the predicates signs around.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467756" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 14:35:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This can&apos;t be fixed in the parser as this all depends on what&apos;s the clustering order and the requested order (if any).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But attaching a patch to fix this (I&apos;ve pushed dtests to make sure we&apos;re good with different variation of clustering order/order by). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467834" author="tjake" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 16:35:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467856" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 16:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
